==English==

===Etymology===
From [[w:Latin|Latin]] ''[[divide et impera]]''

===Phrase===
'''divide and rule'''

#Divide and rule is a combination of political, military and economic [[strategy]] of gaining and maintaining power by breaking up larger concentrations of power into chunks that individually have less power than the one implementing the strategy.

